        "created_at": "2019-07-07T19:37:15.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"153231\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Bollinger hasn\u2019t been more than a mid-term ager in a long while IMO.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Your mid-term is my short-term  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/c/c5b32b76bebaa359b0452ae247b61189ffe5fa7e.gif\" width=\"41\" height=\"40\" alt=\"[tease.gif]\" title=\"tease\" class=\"animated\"></p>\n<p>Last vintage I bought was 2002 and only in magnums.</p>\n<p>Bought twelve mags of the 2008.</p>\n<p>I hope you\u2019re right about the sulphur and higher dosage changing their 20+ year slide into mediocrity. I miss those '60\u2019s and 70\u2019s Bolly\u2019s. Fantastic Champagnes.</p>",
